hostname.description: The Terraform Enterprise hostname to connect to. Defaults to app.terraform.io.

organization.description:
The organization to apply to a resource if one is not defined on
the resource itself

ssl_skip_verify.description: Whether or not to skip certificate verifications.

token.description:
The token used to authenticate with Terraform Enterprise. We recommend omitting
the token which can be set as credentials in the CLI config file.

enforce_mode.description: The enforcement configuration of the policy. For Sentinel, valid values are `hard-mandatory`, `soft-mandatory` and `advisory`. For OPA, Valid values are ``mandatory` and `advisory``

kind.description: The policy-as-code framework for the policy. Valid values are sentinel and opa

organization.description: Name of the organization that this policy belongs to

policy.description: Text of a valid Sentinel or OPA policy

query.description: The OPA query to run. Required for OPA policies

ascii_armor.description: ASCII-armored representation of the GPG key.

created_at.description: The time when the GPG key was created.

organization.description: Name of the organization. If omitted, organization must be defined in the provider config.

updated_at.description: The time when the GPG key was last updated.

block.description: Manages a public key of the GPG key pair used to sign releases of private providers in the private registry.

attr_groups.description: Team Attribute Name specifies the name of the SAML attribute that determines team membership

attr_site_admin.description: Specifies the role for site admin access. Overrides the "Site Admin Role" method

attr_username.description: Username Attribute Name specifies the name of the SAML attribute that determines the user's username

certificate.description: The certificate used for request and assertion signing

debug.description: When sign-on fails and this is enabled, the SAMLResponse XML will be displayed on the login page

enabled.description: Whether or not SAML single sign-on is enabled

idp_cert.description: Identity Provider Certificate specifies the PEM encoded X.509 Certificate as provided by the IdP configuration

private_key.description: The private key used for request and assertion signing

signature_digest_method.description: Signature Digest Method. Must be either `SHA1` or `SHA256`. Defaults to `SHA256`

signature_signing_method.description: Signature Signing Method. Must be either `SHA1` or `SHA256`. Defaults to `SHA256`

site_admin_role.description: Specifies the role for site admin access, provided in the list of roles sent in the Team Attribute Name attribute

slo_endpoint_url.description: Single Log Out URL specifies the HTTPS endpoint on your IdP for single logout requests. This value is provided by the IdP configuration

sso_api_token_session_timeout.description: Specifies the Single Sign On session timeout in seconds. Defaults to 14 days

sso_endpoint_url.description: Single Sign On URL specifies the HTTPS endpoint on your IdP for single sign-on requests. This value is provided by the IdP configuration

team_management_enabled.description: Set it to false if you would rather use Terraform Enterprise to manage team membership

category.description: Whether this is a Terraform or environment variable. Valid values are "terraform" or "env".

readable_value.description: A non-sensitive read-only copy of the variable value, which can be viewed or referenced in plan outputs without being redacted. Will only be present if the variable is not sensitive

enforcement_level.description: The enforcement level of the task. Valid values are `advisory` and `mandatory`.

stage.description: The stage to run the task in. Valid values are `pre_plan`, `post_plan` and `pre_apply`.

task_id.description: The id of the Run task to associate to the Workspace.

workspace_id.description: The id of the workspace to associate the Run task to.

block.description: Additional Workspace settings that override organization defaults

organization.description: The organization to fetch the remote state from.

workspace.description: The workspace to fetch the remote state from.

kind.description: The policy-as-code framework for the policy. Valid values are sentinel and opa

overridable.description: Whether users can override this policy when it fails during a run. Only valid for OPA policies

ascii_armor.description: ASCII-armored representation of the GPG key.

created_at.description: The time when the GPG key was created.

organization.description: Name of the organization. If omitted, organization must be defined in the provider config.

updated_at.description: The time when the GPG key was last updated.

block.description: This data source can be used to retrieve a private registry GPG key.

keys.description: List of GPG keys in the organization.

organization.description: Name of the organization. If omitted, organization must be defined in the provider config.

block.description: This data source can be used to retrieve all private registry GPG keys of an organization.

enforcement_level.description: The enforcement level of the task.

stage.description: Which stage the task will run in.

task_id.description: The id of the run task.
